document.text: We use Fenichel’s reduction to regularize the singular perturbation in existence and
eigenvalue problem in Section 2. In Section 4, we study the resulting regularized traveling wave
problem using functional-analytic methods, using methods developed in [2, 4, 3] to find pulled
and pushed front profiles as well as the transition curve. Section 5 establishes marginal spectral
stability of these fronts thus justifying the pushed and pulled terminology. In Section 6, we briefly
compare the expansions obtained in Theorem 1.2 to those obtained using numerical continuation.
